#: ../../C/CrApTeX.rst:9
msgid ""
"[University of York, England] Term of abuse used to describe TeX and LaTeX "
"when they don't work (when used by TeXhackers), or all the time (by everyone"
" else). The non-TeX-enthusiasts generally dislike it because it is more "
"verbose than other formatters (e.g. :ref:`troff`\\) and because "
"(particularly if the standard Computer Modern fonts are used) it generates "
"vast output files. See :ref:`religious-issues`\\, :ref:`TeX`\\."
msgstr ""
"[英国ヨーク大学] "
"TeXやLaTeXが(TeXハッカーが使う場合に)動かないとき、または(それ以外の誰もが使う場合に)常に、それらをののしるために使われる用語。TeX愛好家でない人々が一般にこれを嫌うのは、他のフォーマッター(たとえば\\"
" :ref:`troff`\\ )よりも冗長であり、また(特に標準のComputer "
"Modernフォントを使う場合)膨大な出力ファイルを生成するためです。\\ :ref:`religious-issues`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`TeX`\\ を参照。"
